{"_id":"0P928eXsERrtQkCJ","name":"Plague of Snakes","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.0P928eXsERrtQkCJ"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"very long","duration":"weeks or until penance","area":"village","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">The sinful often need little more than gentle guidance and a few kind words to mend their ways; but alas, some are relentless in their insubordination. This spell brings a plague of snakes to a large area, which, although not venomous, will appear everywhere in great numbers, and torment the locals as they can. They will have neither rest nor work, and the most sinful will have the worst of it. It is a fair warning to use this spell, although it is more merciful to terminate it once the people repent.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185172,"modifiedTime":1672331714659,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"1qQaMLTtwDOvRW4D","name":"Man-Sheep","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.1qQaMLTtwDOvRW4D"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"short","duration":"permanent","area":"one target","save":"bravery","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">It turns someone with low or average Virtue into the unholy hybrid of man and sheep. The result is vaguely humanoid, fluffy, not to mention herbivorous, peaceful, and wont to bleat a lot instead of talking. What use is there for this? It has not been found out, unless it was meant as some kind of parable.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185172,"modifiedTime":1672331714659,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"2covsBBp3RwcFWLD","name":"Heavenly Choir","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.2covsBBp3RwcFWLD"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"special","area":"hearers","save":"temptation","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">The music of the spheres is brought to the Earth with this word, but only as long as the Cleric continues to sing, or recites from the Holy Writ. Those with high Virtue are healed 1d6+level Hp, and gain +2 to any roll of their choice each round; while those with low Virtue suffer the opposite effect, and a further 1d4 Hp damage every round.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185172,"modifiedTime":1672331714659,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"2kI6qYnNZQtjiRhF","name":"True Apothecary","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.2kI6qYnNZQtjiRhF"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"touch","duration":"instantaneous","area":"one person","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">It is a very effective healing spell, for it not only returns 3d6 Hp and 1 more per level, but it is also useful against diseases and poisons; and with longer resting, even mortal wounds. This may not return the lives of the dead, although for certain great afflictions like the plague, hunchback, Cholera Morbus, the French disease or similar, it may be either a treatment or at least a pain-ease. This healing ability is also the power of major relics, and it is usually learned in spell form where they are being kept.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185172,"modifiedTime":1672331714659,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"5rMF7nW1XTLWwVXn","name":"Miasmatic Mire","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.5rMF7nW1XTLWwVXn"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"-","area":"one group","save":"deftness","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">Sin always leads the errant towards Hell, and this spell shows them the fastest way there is. If they fail their saving throws, they will sink into the ground as they are, everyone according to their sins: those with average Virtue to their ankles; those with low Virtue to their knees; and those with 3 or lower Virtue to their waist. From the first, someone may free themselves with a Hard Strength or Escape Artist check; from the second, they must dig for a quarter hour; and from the third, for some hours. It is useless on rocky ground.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185172,"modifiedTime":1672331714659,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"CRNRJgHxt0xZ0jAr","name":"Ephemeral Foundation","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.CRNRJgHxt0xZ0jAr"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"quarter of an hour","area":"around oneself","save":"deftness","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">Those without the firm moral compass of high Virtue must make a Deftness save or be knocked about like so many chess pieces, suffering 3d6 Hp damage and losing 1d3 rounds worth of actions. If they would get up, they must roll another save, or remain fallen. Characters in a state of a high Virtue receive +3 to their AC. It distinguishes not between friend or foe: but only betwixt the righteous and the unworthy.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185172,"modifiedTime":1672331714659,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"HBwLmIsj4dvAIcot","name":"Horns of Jericho","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.HBwLmIsj4dvAIcot"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"long","duration":"quarter of an hour","area":"hearers","save":"bravery","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">Mighty horns resound in the sky, aiding the Lord&rsquo;s servants in multiple known ways. If enemy hosts, brigands, or Heaven forbid the Devil&rsquo;s own would approach, there is a great clamour, and those who are weak in spirit run like cowards; while those who have a low Virtue, must cover their ears and cease fighting at once. The harmonies, which have undone the walls of Jericho in their time, can even today bring down lesser stone barriers, clean out collapsed passages, or batter down gates, so that someone who is stuck can escape unharmed: but it is also useful to make buildings totter and collapse into rubble.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185172,"modifiedTime":1672331714659,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"HwKRzaReNJcQbhQr","name":"Deus Vult!","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.HwKRzaReNJcQbhQr"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"-","duration":"2 + 1 round/level","area":"a company","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">It was the prayer of the crusaders, but it remains useful in the time of new heresies. Every true Christian around the Cleric receives +1 to their attacks, damage, and AC; +2 if they have high Virtue, and +3 if it is 21. All unbelievers in the area, whether heretic, Mohammedan, Jew or pagan, must roll a Temptation saving throw or they are only able to defend themselves; and if they roll very badly, throw themselves on the ground and discard their weapons, or run in panic. This is indeed so for all who are not Christians, even if they were the Cleric&rsquo;s trusted friends; and likewise, it has an effect on all Students, unless they have confessed their sins and achieved a state of high Virtue.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185172,"modifiedTime":1672331714659,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"IndPY4D2dkRajEAW","name":"Witnessing of the Oak","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.IndPY4D2dkRajEAW"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"instantaneous, or one day","area":"oak tree","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">This is used if a great danger threatens the congregation. The Cleric should gather great and small under the tree, and call on the majestic oak to obey in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ and All Saints. Then, the tree falls and strikes dead those of the flock who contemplate evil; or with the other use, keeps all safe from any foe for one day under its crown. But it might be that there will be many false ones to die this</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">way, or that the foes will surround the tree and wait for the end of the spell, for there is no way in, but there is no way out either. In conclusion, it is hazardous to use, and few dare to do it.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185173,"modifiedTime":1672331714660,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"TTha4S7xtd2pcqeP","name":"Protective Friend","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.TTha4S7xtd2pcqeP"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"-","duration":"one day per level","area":"one person","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">The angels of Heaven and other invisible forces will stand watch over the chosen, who may not be harmed in either body or Virtue in their rest. Yet the angelic guardians cannot abide by any mischief, and if the subject is of low Virtue, or they commit a sin worth 2 or more points, they abandon their charge.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185173,"modifiedTime":1672331714660,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"VEK7xYi8MKAGQ4Mv","name":"Armour of Virtue","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.VEK7xYi8MKAGQ4Mv"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"touch","duration":"quarter of an hour","area":"one person","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">Those who are strong of heart and noble of spirit are dressed in armour surrounded by a halo of pure light: this grants an AC bonus equal to their Virtue above 14, and for a 21, one more point. It also increases all saving throws by +1 at 14 Virtue, +2 at 17 Virtue, and +3 at 21 Virtue. If the target is already wearing armour, the stronger value prevails, but they still receive the saving throw bonus.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185173,"modifiedTime":1672331714660,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"WL7ESsMOpU9iRRmy","name":"Stay!","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.WL7ESsMOpU9iRRmy"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"long","duration":"instantaneous","area":"hearers","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">A single word will stop mill, marching army, lifted sword, avalanche, falling man and holiday procession, and there are none who could resist it. But let them be of good judgement who would use it: for if the command would lead into sin, it will fall threefold on the speaker&rsquo;s Virtue.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185173,"modifiedTime":1672331714660,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"WjCLiIMBWMDjNEPQ","name":"Relinquishing Hand","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.WjCLiIMBWMDjNEPQ"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"long","duration":"instantaneous","area":"one target","save":"temptation","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">There is nothing more terrible than the Mother Church enraged: the hand that nurtures and accepts can, in a time of need, strike sin with exemplary strictness. This spell can be used on those who have committed grave deeds against the divine and mortal order: if they fail their save, they may not enter a church or hallowed ground until they have regretted their terrible deed, and done atonement.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185173,"modifiedTime":1672331714660,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"dZEZxmGOZbNEKTkk","name":"Weary Dust","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.dZEZxmGOZbNEKTkk"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"instantaneous","area":"before oneself, and around","save":"bravery","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">All things and beings taken from dust, and beyond their allotted time must save immediately or crumble into dust. It is very useful against the undead, but it is not always effective on the stronger ones, as some of them still have duties to accomplish in this world.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185173,"modifiedTime":1672331714660,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"gfajFvomSp6sYlJK","name":"Endowment of the Word","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.gfajFvomSp6sYlJK"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"touch","duration":"< 1 month","area":"one person","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">This formula lies under a cardinal&rsquo;s seal anywhere it is found, to be opened only at the hour of great need and danger. This way, one of the spells of a holy edifice can be planted within someone&rsquo;s mind, in a way that it is lost in its place of origin, but the subject can recall it again and again every day, making him or her the carrier of the Word. If they so desire, they can dissolve the binding at the morning or evening</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">prayer, but if they should suffer accidental death, there is a 1:6 probability the spell will be lost. Needless to say, this favour is like a precious treasure, and even heavier responsibility comes with it.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185173,"modifiedTime":1672331714660,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"jKpDflii4fGdzFoR","name":"Mark of Cain","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.jKpDflii4fGdzFoR"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"short","duration":"forever","area":"one person","save":"bravery","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">It is only useful against the most hardened sinners, with a Virtue no more than 3. If they fail their save, a burning mark will appear on their forehead, which immediately causes 3d6+6 damage and remains in place until they die. If the spell should kill the subject, they instantaneously burn to ashes, and their smouldering bones are dragged down to Hell by devils with shovels and pitchforks. Using this spell is a most pious and exemplary undertaking.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185173,"modifiedTime":1672331714660,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"jOxzngJaR3Yhs2Mg","name":"Pacem in Terris","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.jOxzngJaR3Yhs2Mg"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"long","duration":"one day and one night","area":"in hearing distance","save":"temptation","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">It is very nice words which speak for peace, and those who hear them shall cast their weapons on the ground to wait and listen. Even the wild beasts and the creatures of Hell will lie down, for Love is before all. This is equivalent to a confession, and restores 1d3+2 Virtue. The peace will last one day and one night, and if it is uttered in or before battle, it will cease or never take place. Someone who uses this formula will be as weak as a new-born babe for seven days. If only these words were proclaimed from every pulpit! &ndash; but alas, they are nowhere to be found.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185173,"modifiedTime":1672331714660,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"qhMoeSzO9VrPT0Jq","name":"Extranatural Spectacle","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.qhMoeSzO9VrPT0Jq"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"10 minutes","area":"around oneself","save":"bravery","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">The likeness of beautiful and terrible things, perhaps out of the Revelations or other similar writings, is manifested on the sky: and most will consider this a momentous occasion, while others, less sure of faith in their state of low Virtue, will experience confusion and the icy fear of Death. Those in a state of high Virtue, will be reassured, and the few whose life and faith are one (21 Virtue), stand proud. Many such signs in the sky have been seen since Christendom has not been whole: and some fear there will be more terrible ones yet while it stays unmended.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185174,"modifiedTime":1672331714660,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"w6Ve7fiyZ8ORsCWE","name":"Great Silence","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.w6Ve7fiyZ8ORsCWE"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"until absolution or 1 month","area":"one space","save":"bravery","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">The silence before Creation is brought upon an open or closed space, which might be as large as a small village. Thereafter, only the Word written inside the Holy Bible can sound within; and only from those who can roll a successful saving throw. Let them prepare well, those who would turn to this: for if they misuse it, they must roll a save themselves, or be struck by the spell of The Mute.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185174,"modifiedTime":1672331714660,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"wPHPQzcAAE8k0bH1","name":"Quid Pro Quo","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-3.wPHPQzcAAE8k0bH1"}},"system":{"level":"3","class":"cleric","range":"long","duration":"as long as needed","area":"one person","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">The consequences of the considered deed are oft returned with interest to the one who had planned it: be it good or evil. This saying is manifested by the Cleric spell that proves the saying by the inscrutable will of Providence. The lesson can come for a current or future deed; sudden action or well-planned scheme; but when it is meted out, it will come quickly, and everyone will see its morals. Those who perceive the spell&rsquo;s essence are unaffected, for they are not an honest soul &ndash; and woe to anyone who would abuse it for the benefit of themselves or their company!</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329185174,"modifiedTime":1672331714660,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
